&gt;&gt;&gt;    &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://support.google.com/meet/answer/14808197"&gt;https://support.google.com/meet/answer/14808197&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;    - WPT tests
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; We plan to add these once we have a clearer idea of what the final
&gt;&gt;&gt; shape of the API surface will be. This is likely to happen after the August
&gt;&gt;&gt; 27 WG Meeting &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://www.w3.org/2011/04/webrtc/wiki/August_27_2024"&gt;https://www.w3.org/2011/04/webrtc/wiki/August_27_2024&lt;/a&gt;&gt;,
&gt;&gt;&gt; where this API will be discussed.
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Can you work on making progress on gathering signals, writing WPTs, and
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; also clarify whether the spec has been updated to the new design?
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; The current version of the spec reflects what is currently shipping in
&gt;&gt;&gt; the OT. We'll update it once 1) the new additions are ready for inclusion
&gt;&gt;&gt; in the OT and 2) we discuss them in the WG meeting later this month.
